==保护工作==
[[Image:HluHluwe.jpg|thumb]]

===非洲野犬===
1981年，纳塔尔公园局（现Ezemvelo KZN Wildlife）已重新引进园区[[非洲野犬|非洲野犬]]。总共在保护区释放了23条狗，其中大部分是在动物园饲养的。然而带来的成果有限，引进野犬以后，其数量浮动在3至30只之间。<ref>{{cite journal|url = http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg14419523.900-wild-at-heart-the-africn-wild-dog-long-presecuted-as-vermin-is-down-to-a-few-thousand-is-too-late-for-science-to-come-to-the-rescue-of-this-species.html|title = Wild at heart: The African wild dog, long presecuted as vermin, is down to a few thousand; is it too late for science to come to the rescue of this species?|work = New Scientist|publisher = Reed Business Information Ltd|last = Ginsberg|first = Joshua|last2 = Cole|first2 = Mary|date = 19 November 1994|issue = 1952|page = 34|accessdate = 2015-08-09|subscription = yes|journal = |archive-date = 2014-08-15|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140815112649/http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg14419523.900-wild-at-heart-the-africn-wild-dog-long-presecuted-as-vermin-is-down-to-a-few-thousand-is-too-late-for-science-to-come-to-the-rescue-of-this-species.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>

===犀牛===
[[Image:Umfolozi_Rhino.jpg|thumb]]
该公园是犀牛保护的发源地，保护这个物种不至于[[绝灭|灭绝]]（从1900年全球不到20只到今天有1万多只犀牛）。20世纪50年代和60年代，园区成为世界闻名的白犀牛保护区。<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.sa-venues.com/game-reserves/kzn_hluhluwe-umfolozi.htm|title = Hluhluwe Imfolozi Park|publisher = SA-Venues.com|accessdate = 2015-08-11|archive-date = 2018-11-26|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20181126071010/https://www.sa-venues.com/game-reserves/kzn_hluhluwe-umfolozi.htm|dead-url = no}}</ref> 该公园保护了濒临灭绝的白犀牛。今天，有超过1600只白犀牛和数百只的野生动物被转移到世界各地的动物保护区。<ref name = where/> 这一计划的胜利果实最近随着偷猎犀牛行为的增加的破坏。最近这次威胁不仅在公园内引起极大的关注，还引起了全国犀牛保护者的关注。<ref>{{cite newspaper| url=http://www.africanconservation.org/wildlife-news/south-africa-bloody-butchers-more-rhino-poached-in-hluhluwe-imfolozi-park-2| title=South Africa: Bloody butchers - More rhino poached in Hluhluwe-Imfolozi Park| work=[http://www.zululandobserver.co.za Zululand Observer]| date=3 December 2010| via=[[African_Conservation_Foundation|African Conservation Foundation]]| accessdate=2015-08-11| archive-date=2017-10-19| archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019215655/https://www.africanconservation.org/wildlife-news/south-africa-bloody-butchers-more-rhino-poached-in-hluhluwe-imfolozi-park-2| dead-url=no}}</ref>

